Analysis of the Main Target Image
---------------------------------
1) Overall Count and Layering

 •  The scene comprises two separate constructions (a tall “tower” on the left and a lower grouping on the right), using a total of 18 blocks.  
 •  The tall tower (left) is built in six vertical “layers”:  
    – Layer 1 (bottom): one yellow rectangular block laid flat.  
    – Layer 2: four small red quarter‐circle blocks arranged to form a circular “window” in the center.  
    – Layer 3: one yellow rectangular block laid flat.  
    – Layer 4: two upright orange cylinders supporting the next layer.  
    – Layer 5: one yellow rectangular block laid flat.  
    – Layer 6 (top): one orange triangular wedge forming the roof.  

 •  The lower structure (right) can be viewed in four layers:  
    – Layer 1 (bottom): one red triangular wedge and one green rectangular block side by side, plus an orange cylinder standing just to the right.  
    – Layer 2: on top of the green block, one yellow cube and one blue cube filling out a 2×1 space.  
    – Layer 3: atop the orange cylinder, one red arch block.  
    – Layer 4 (top): two small yellow half‐cylinders side by side, forming a curved “roof” above the red arch block.  

2) Which Dictionary Blocks Are Used
-----------------------------------
Below is the complete list of needed blocks (by their dictionary index), along with the quantity of each.  No rotations other than what is shown in the dictionary have been used.

 •  #1  (Red arch, half‐circle underside L–R) … 1×  
 •  #3  (Red quarter‐circle piece) … 2×  
 •  #4  (Red quarter‐circle piece, mirror of #3) … 2×  
 •  #5  (Blue cube) … 1×  
 •  #7  (Yellow cube) … 1×  
 •  #8  (Green rectangular prism) … 1×  
 •  #9  (Yellow rectangular prism) … 3×  
 •  #10 (Orange cylinder) … 3×  
 •  #12 (Small yellow half‐cylinder, axis front–back) … 2×  
 •  #13 (Orange triangular wedge) … 1×  
 •  #14 (Red triangular wedge) … 1×  

3) Step‑by‑Step Assembly Order
------------------------------
Below is one possible order in which these 18 pieces could be placed:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 9
  Step2:  Move block with index 3
  Step3:  Move block with index 4
  Step4:  Move block with index 3
  Step5:  Move block with index 4
  Step6:  Move block with index 9
  Step7:  Move block with index 10
  Step8:  Move block with index 10
  Step9:  Move block with index 9
  Step10: Move block with index 13
  Step11: Move block with index 14
  Step12: Move block with index 8
  Step13: Move block with index 7
  Step14: Move block with index 5
  Step15: Move block with index 10
  Step16: Move block with index 1
  Step17: Move block with index 12
  Step18: Move block with index 12
}

Following this sequence will recreate the two sub‐structures exactly as shown in the target image, matching both color and orientation of each block.
